						               													<description>&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#147;&amp;#227;&amp;#130;&amp;#185;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#136;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#173;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#187;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#149;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#170;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#131;&amp;#227;&amp;#131;&amp;#151; (Bistro Flip: A Dinner by Heaven Sent Chefs) is a Japanese card game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;ldquo;Ding ding!&amp;rdquo; Ring the bell, and call out &amp;ldquo;ORDER PLEASE!&amp;rdquo; and let the game begin!&amp;#10;Select and match up the ingredients. Add in your own personal touch.... Cook it up and hope for the best.... FLIP!&amp;#10;What fun and unique dish did you make? Was it what you were hoping for?&amp;#10;Create interesting and original dishes and have a belly laugh at what comes up! A fun, lively party game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Chef players must create 3 meals to suit the requirements of the Diner player.&amp;#10;The person at the end of the rounds with the most points is the winner.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;HOW TO PLAY:&amp;#10;The Diner player requests a meal.&amp;#10;Ingredients are drafted, so Chef players should pick wisely as you may end up with ingredients that may not work.&amp;#10;Additional randomized Chef's Style cards are dealt to each player.&amp;#10;Chef players plan their meals, once the Diner calls &amp;quot;TIME!&amp;quot;, everyone must stop planning and present their recipes.&amp;#10;Show the cards, appeal other than cards with oral presentation to the Diner. But the dish is not completed yet. When they present their recipe for each course, they FLIP over 1 more face down card to complete the dish...&amp;#10;Will it be a perfect match or something no one wants to try?&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
